Music producer, Michael Ajereh aka Don Jazzy has broken his silence after losing his mother. The Mavin Records boss had informed that his mother died after battling cancer. Don Jazzy, in a post on Sunday, thanked his numerous supporters and well-wishers for their various supports.   Tiwa Savage reveals man behind ‘Somebody’s son’ hit track     Skit maker Carter Efe tops Apple Music with debut single     BBNaija Level Up: Doyin kisses Cyph   He said: “Experience is truly the best teacher. Before I thank everyone for their calls, visits and messages, I need to first apologize to my friends and associates who lost loved ones and don’t think I was there enough for them. “I know better now and sadly, I had to learn the hard way. “Thank you everyone for your support over the last few days. It has meant the world to me. Funeral details will be shared once finalized. “We will also share links so you can join us remotely from wherever you are. Thank you again guys.”